{
  "original_content": "# Exercise: Formatting a Long Document\n\nIn this task, you practice using automatic functions in managing a long document.\n\n## Task Steps\n\n1. **Open the base text:** Use the file `Base text: Digital Photography.md`.\n2. **Headings:** \n    * Use the **Heading 1** style for main headings.\n    * Use the **Heading 2** style for subheadings.\n3. **Cover page:** \n    * Add a blank page at the beginning (*Ctrl + Enter*).\n    * Create a cover page with the title of the work, your name, and the date.\n4. **Table of Contents:**\n    * Add an automatic table of contents on its own page after the cover page.\n5. **Page numbering:**\n    * Add page numbers to the footer on the right.\n    * Numbering may only start after the table of contents. (Tip: Use a section break).\n6. **Images:**\n    * Add at least two images related to the topic in the text.\n    * Add automatic captions to the images.\n7. **Save:** Save as `Long_document_photography.docx`.\n\n---\n**Goal:** Create a professional and readable whole in which automatic lists work correctly.",
